{"meta":{"title":"Moroni 1","canonicalUrl":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/1?lang=eng","contentType":"text/html","audio":[{"mediaUrl":"https://media2.ldscdn.org/assets/scriptures/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ/2015-11-2300-moroni-01-female-voice-64k-eng.mp3","voice":{"name":"female"}},{"mediaUrl":"https://media2.ldscdn.org/assets/scriptures/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ/2015-11-2300-moroni-01-male-voice-64k-eng.mp3","voice":{"name":"male"}}],"pageAttributes":{"data-asset-id":"4cc48df2ea969ff61326326dfb6e80ff8776abe7","data-aid":"128358838","data-aid-version":"6","data-content-type":"chapter","data-uri":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/1","lang":"eng","data-orig-id":"4cc48df2ea969ff61326326dfb6e80ff8776abe7","xmlns:xsi":"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"}},"content":{"head":{"page-meta-social":{"pageMeta":{"title":"Moroni 1","description":"Moroni writes for the benefit of the Lamanites—The Nephites who will not deny Christ are put to death. About A.D. 401–21."},"pageSocial":{"title":"Moroni 1","description":"Moroni writes for the benefit of the Lamanites—The Nephites who will not deny Christ are put to death. About A.D. 401–21."}},"links":[{"type":"array","rel":"stylesheet","orig-type":"text/css","href":"css/style_classic-scripture.css"}],"scripts":[]},"body":"<header>\n<h1 data-aid=\"128358839\" id=\"title1\"><span class=\"dominant\">The Book of Moroni</span></h1>\n<p class=\"title-number\" data-aid=\"128358840\" id=\"title_number1\">Chapter 1</p>\n<p class=\"study-summary\" data-aid=\"128358841\" id=\"study_summary1\">Moroni writes for the benefit of the Lamanites—The Nephites who will not deny Christ are put to death. About <small>A.D.</small> 401–21.</p>\n</header>\n<div class=\"body-block\">\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358842\" id=\"p1\"><span class=\"verse-number\">1 </span>Now I, Moroni, after having made an end of abridging the account of the people of Jared, I had supposed <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note1a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>not</a> to have written more, but I have not as yet perished; and I make not myself known to the Lamanites lest they should destroy me.</p>\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358843\" id=\"p2\"><span class=\"verse-number\">2 </span>For behold, their <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note2a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>wars</a> are exceedingly fierce among themselves; and because of their <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note2b\"><sup class=\"marker\">b</sup>hatred</a> they <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note2c\"><sup class=\"marker\">c</sup>put to death</a> every Nephite that will not deny the Christ.</p>\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358844\" id=\"p3\"><span class=\"verse-number\">3 </span>And I, Moroni, will not <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note3a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>deny</a> the Christ; wherefore, I wander whithersoever I can for the safety of mine own life.</p>\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358845\" id=\"p4\"><span class=\"verse-number\">4 </span>Wherefore, I write a few more things, contrary to that which I had supposed; for I had supposed not to have written any more; but I write a few more things, that perhaps they may be of <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note4a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>worth</a> unto my brethren, the Lamanites, in some future day, according to the will of the Lord.</p>\n</div>\n<footer class=\"study-notes\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"chapter\">\n<li data-marker=\"1\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"verse\">\n<li data-marker=\"1\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note1a\" data-full-marker=\"1a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358846\" id=\"note1a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/morm/8.5?lang=eng#p5\">Morm. 8:5</a>; <a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.1-2?lang=eng#p1\">Moro. 10:1 (1–2)</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"2\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note2a\" data-full-marker=\"2a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358847\" id=\"note2a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/12.20-23?lang=eng#p21\">1 Ne. 12:21 (20–23)</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"b\" id=\"note2b\" data-full-marker=\"2b\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358848\" id=\"note2b_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/hate?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Hate</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"c\" id=\"note2c\" data-full-marker=\"2c\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358849\" id=\"note2c_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/45.14?lang=eng#p14\">Alma 45:14</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"3\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note3a\" data-full-marker=\"3a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358850\" id=\"note3a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/nt/matt/10.32-33?lang=eng#p33\">Matt. 10:33 (32–33)</a>; <a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/29.5?lang=eng#p5\">3 Ne. 29:5</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"4\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note4a\" data-full-marker=\"4a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358851\" id=\"note4a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/3.11-12,19?lang=eng#p12\">2 Ne. 3:12 (11–12, 19)</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</footer>","associated":{"title_number1":[{"sizes":"250px","alt":"Mormon Bids Farewell to a Once Great Nation","aspectRatio":"1.4349775784753362","height":"223","width":"320","missingAsset":"false","assetId":"5220c52e82405490705ddef18e279cbffd7788ab","srcset":"https://assets.ldscdn.org/c7/af/c7afb59cb16